    <h1>How to use</h1>
    <h2>Basic use</h2>
    <p>This is the most basic use.</p>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <InputFileExtended TargetToPostFile="files" @ref="Files"
                               CleanOnSuccessUpload="true"
                               ButtonShow="ShowUpload"
                               OnSave="Save" />

        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
                <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
                    <button class="nav-link @Basic1" @onclick="()=> ChangeTab(0)" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="home" aria-selected="true">Basic</button>
                </li>
                <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
                    <button class="nav-link @Basic2" @onclick="()=> ChangeTab(1)" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="profile" aria-selected="false">With Upload Button</button>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tab-content">
                <div class="tab-pane @Basic1" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="home-tab">
                    <p>This example is the most basic use. Only can select image and show a preview.</p>
                    <pre>
<code>&lt;InputFileExtended /&gt;

@@code{
    //No need nothing else
}
</code>
        </pre>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane @Basic2" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="profile-tab">
                    <p>This is the most basic example with upload button and send to the server.</p>
                    <h2>Properties</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>TargetToPostFile</strong> Url relative or absolute to send the file with a <var>POST</var> action</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Messages log: @Messages</p>
                    <pre>
<code>&lt;InputFileExtended 
    TargetToPostFile="http://myserver.com/upload"            
    ButtonShow="true"
    /&gt;

@@code{
    //No need nothing else
}
</code>
        </pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>